ARABIC: لَمْ يَطْمِثْهُنَّ إِنسٌ قَبْلَهُمْ وَلَا جَآنٌّ

ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_0: Untouched before them by either man or jinn.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_1: Undeflowered by man or by jinn before them, --
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_2: No man or jinn ever touched them before.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_3: - untouched by jinn or mankind before.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_4: Untouched by any man or jinn, before them.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_5: Whom never deflowered a human before nor Jinn.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_6: Man has not touched them before them nor jinni.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_7: untouched before them by any man or jinn --
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_8: Whom neither man nor jinni will have touched before them -
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_9: Whom neither a man or jinn had ever touched before them.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_10: There hath deflowered them neither man nor jinn.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_11: Whom no human has touched before, nor jinn.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_12: Whom no man or Jinn before them has touched;-
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_13: Whom no man or jinn yatmithhunna (has opened their hymens with sexual intercourse) before them.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_14: Neither human nor jinn will have touched them before.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_15: Whom no human has touched before, nor jinn.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_16: Untouched before them by man or jinni -
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_17: [55:74] Untouched by any man before them, before these [soon-to-be] spouses of theirs, or jinn.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_18: Whom neither man nor jinn will have touched before them) before their husbands
